Jamaica has been authorized topurchase about 56,000 tonnes of U.S. wheat under an existing PL480 agreement, the U.S. Agriculture Department said.    It may buy the wheat, valued at 7.0 mln dlrs, between March25 and August 341 and ship it from U.S. ports and/or Canadiantransshipment points by September 30, 1987. Reuter&#3;